Q)What is a Process?

A process is an instance of a running program. Each process has a unique Process ID (PID) assigned by the system.

Command	Description
ps aux			Lists all running processes.
top				Shows real-time process information.
htop			Interactive process viewer (if installed).
pidof <process_name>	Finds the PID of a running process.
kill <PID>				Terminates a process using its PID.
kill -9 <PID>			Forcefully terminates a process.
pkill <process_name>	Kills a process by name.
systemctl status <service>	Checks the status of a service.




